{"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"],"kind":"relationships","type":"inheritsFrom","title":"Inherits From"},{"title":"Conforming Types","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef"],"kind":"relationships","type":"conformingTypes"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SourceFuncsProtocol"},{"text":" : ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"PointerWrapper","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For idle sources, the prepare and check functions always return ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to indicate that the source is always ready to be processed. The prepare"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"function also returns a timeout value of 0 to ensure that the "},{"code":"poll()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" call","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"doesn’t block (since that would be time wasted which could have been spent","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"running the idle function).","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For timeout sources, the prepare and check functions both return "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"if the timeout interval has expired. The prepare function also returns","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a timeout value to ensure that the "},{"code":"poll()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" call doesn’t block too long","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and miss the next timeout.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For file descriptor sources, the prepare function typically returns ","type":"text"},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"since it must wait until "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"poll()"},{"type":"text","text":" has been called before it knows whether"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"any events need to be processed. It sets the returned timeout to -1 to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"indicate that it doesn’t mind how long the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"poll()"},{"type":"text","text":" call blocks. In the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"check function, it tests the results of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"poll()"},{"text":" call to see if the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"required condition has been met, and returns ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":" if so.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying "},{"code":"GSourceFuncs","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Alternatively, use ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef"},{"text":" as a lighweight, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"type":"text","text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"title":"SourceFuncsProtocol","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SourceFuncsProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"roleHeading":"Protocol","externalID":"s:4GLib19SourceFuncsProtocolP","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SourceFuncsProtocol"}],"symbolKind":"protocol"},"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSourceFuncs"},{"type":"text","text":" struct contains a table of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"functions used to handle event sources in a generic manner.","type":"text"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/sourcefuncsprotocol"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"topicSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol\/check","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol\/dispatch","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol\/finalize","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol\/prepare"],"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties"},{"generated":true,"title":"Instance Methods","anchor":"Instance-Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol\/sourceRemoveByFuncs(userData:)"]}],"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/MainContext":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","role":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GMainContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" struct is an opaque data","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"type representing a set of sources to be handled in a main loop.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"MainContext","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/maincontext","title":"MainContext","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/SourceFuncsProtocol/sourceRemoveByFuncs(userData:)":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourcefuncsprotocol\/sourceremovebyfuncs(userdata:)","title":"sourceRemoveByFuncs(userData:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"sourceRemoveByFuncs","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"userData","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"gpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol\/sourceRemoveByFuncs(userData:)","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Removes a source from the default main loop context given the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"source functions and user data.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/SourceFuncs":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"code":"GSourceFuncs","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" struct contains a table of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"functions used to handle event sources in a generic manner.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourcefuncs","kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SourceFuncs","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"SourceFuncs","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncs","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SourceFuncs","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/sourceRemove":{"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/sourceRemove","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"let","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"sourceRemove","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Int32","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:s5Int32V"}],"title":"sourceRemove","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourceremove","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this macro as the return value of a [callback"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFunc","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] to remove"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the [struct"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] from the main loop."}],"type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/SourceFuncsProtocol":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SourceFuncsProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol","title":"SourceFuncsProtocol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourcefuncsprotocol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSourceFuncs"},{"type":"text","text":" struct contains a table of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"functions used to handle event sources in a generic manner.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SourceFuncsProtocol"}],"type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/SourceFuncsProtocol/finalize":{"abstract":[{"text":"Called when the source is finalized. At this point,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the source will have been destroyed, had its callback cleared, and have"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"been removed from its [struct"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","type":"reference"},{"text":"], but it will still have","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"its final reference count, so methods can be called on it from within"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"this function. This may be "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":", in which case the effect is as if the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"function does nothing and returns."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol\/finalize","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourcefuncsprotocol\/finalize","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"finalize"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GSourceFuncsFinalizeFunc","text":"GSourceFuncsFinalizeFunc"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"type":"topic","title":"finalize","role":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/SourceFuncsProtocol/prepare":{"title":"prepare","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol\/prepare","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"prepare"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"GSourceFuncsPrepareFunc","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GSourceFuncsPrepareFunc"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Called before all the file descriptors are polled. If","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the source can determine that it is ready here (without waiting for the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"results of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"poll()"},{"text":" call) it should return ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":". It can also return"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"timeout_"},{"type":"text","text":" value which should be the maximum timeout (in milliseconds)"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"which should be passed to the ","type":"text"},{"code":"poll()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" call. The actual timeout used will"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"be -1 if all sources returned -1, or it will be the minimum of all","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"timeout_"},{"type":"text","text":" values returned which were >= 0.  Since 2.36 this may"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"be "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", in which case the effect is as if the function always returns"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"text":" with a timeout of -1.  If ","type":"text"},{"code":"prepare","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" returns a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"timeout and the source also has a ready time set, then the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"lower of the two will be used."}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourcefuncsprotocol\/prepare","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/SourceFuncsProtocol/dispatch":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol\/dispatch","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Called to dispatch the event source, after it has returned"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" in either its "},{"code":"prepare","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or its "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"check"},{"text":" function, or if a ready time","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"has been reached. The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dispatch"},{"type":"text","text":" function receives a callback function and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"user data. The callback function may be "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":" if the source was never","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"connected to a callback using [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Source.set_callback"},{"type":"text","text":"]. The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"dispatch","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" function should call the callback function with "},{"code":"user_data","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"whatever additional parameters are needed for this type of event source.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The return value of the ","type":"text"},{"code":"dispatch","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" function should be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[const","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/sourceRemove"},{"text":"] if the source should be removed or","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[const"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/sourceContinue","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"] to keep it.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"dispatch","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GSourceFuncsDispatchFunc","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GSourceFuncsDispatchFunc"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"type":"topic","title":"dispatch","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourcefuncsprotocol\/dispatch","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib","kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","abstract":[],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","role":"collection"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/SourceFuncsRef":{"title":"SourceFuncsRef","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsRef","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourcefuncsref","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"SourceFuncsRef","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSourceFuncs"},{"type":"text","text":" struct contains a table of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"functions used to handle event sources in a generic manner."}],"type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SourceFuncsRef","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/SourceFuncsProtocol/check":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourcefuncsprotocol\/check","title":"check","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"check","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GSourceFuncsCheckFunc","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GSourceFuncsCheckFunc"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFuncsProtocol\/check","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Called after all the file descriptors are polled. The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"source should return "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" if it is ready to be dispatched. Note that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"some time may have passed since the previous prepare function was called,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"so the source should be checked again here.  Since 2.36 this may"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":", in which case the effect is as if the function always returns"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/sourceContinue":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/sourceContinue","fragments":[{"text":"let","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"sourceContinue","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gboolean","text":"gboolean","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/sourcecontinue","kind":"symbol","title":"sourceContinue","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this macro as the return value of a [callback"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceFunc","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] to leave"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the [struct"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] in the main loop."}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/PointerWrapper":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PointerWrapper"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/pointerwrapper","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"PointerWrapper"}],"kind":"symbol","title":"PointerWrapper","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Protocol for GLib types that wrap pointers."}]}}}